          <h4>How do you confirm a hand-raised grey seller is legitimate?</h4>
          <p>You don't have to trust your gut — you can check three things in about a minute, and a real breeder will happily wait while you do.</p>
          <h5>The three checks that expose a fake breeder fast</h5>
          <p>Ask for the USDA license and look it up; request a live video call with the bird and today's date in frame; and reverse-image-search the listing photos to catch stolen pictures. A scammer fails at least one of these every time.</p>
