        <!-- ===== 10 · CONGO OR TIMNEH ===== -->
        <section id="congotimneh" class="sec">
          <h2>Should your hand-raised grey be a Congo or a Timneh?</h2>
          <p class="opener">Both subspecies leave our nursery hand-raised the exact same way, so this choice is about fit, not quality. Because the two greys differ in size, tail color and tempo, the honest answer depends on your home — and we're happy to talk it through rather than push the pricier bird.</p>
          <img class="sec-img inf-img" src={IMG + "congo-or-timneh-hand-raised-fast-facts.webp"} srcset={IMG + "congo-or-timneh-hand-raised-fast-facts-760.webp 760w, " + IMG + "congo-or-timneh-hand-raised-fast-facts.webp 1408w"} sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1408" height="768" loading="lazy" alt="Fast-facts comparison of hand-raised Congo African Grey with a red tail and hand-raised Timneh African Grey with a maroon tail" />
          <h3>Congo vs Timneh at a glance</h3>
          <p>The Congo is the larger, red-tailed grey with the headline vocabulary; the Timneh is smaller, maroon-tailed, often a shade calmer and an earlier talker. If you're still weighing it, <a href="/congo-vs-timneh-african-grey/">our Congo vs Timneh comparison breaks the decision down point by point</a> so you can match the grey to your household.</p>
        </section>

