          <div class="fs-video">
            <video controls preload="none" poster={IMG + "hero-mark-hand-scratch-grey.webp"} width="1280" height="720">
              <source src="/images/congo-page/congo-african-grey-roys-eating-video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
              Your browser doesn't support embedded video — <a href="/available/roys/">meet Roys on his page instead</a>.
            </video>
            <p class="vcap">Roys, one of our hand-raised Congo greys, eating on camera. Ask us for a live call with any bird above.</p>
          </div>
          <h3>Real video, filmed against today's date</h3>
          <p>On request we'll film the bird you're considering with today's date in frame, so you can confirm the grey is real, present and healthy before you commit a cent.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="seam-wrap" role="presentation"><img class="seam" src={seam} alt="" loading="lazy" width="182" height="60" /></div>

        <!-- ===== 15 · FAMILIES ===== -->
        <section id="families" class="sec">
          <h2>What do buyers of our hand-raised greys say?</h2>
          <p class="opener">The best test of a hand-raised bird is how it settles in after the excitement fades — so here are two families in their own words. Because these are verified C.A.Gs buyers, their stories sit here unedited, the way they sent them.</p>
